fixed ICS bug with content flashes

it seems that -webkit-transform was to blame for content flashes on load
(in ICS loading the app would not show the main page until a touch
event was triggered)

prevent horizontal scrolling in android ics

the combined padding left and right and width 100% is causing horizontal
scrolling in android ics so removing width

separate ios specific css interfering with android ics

in ics -webkit-overflow-scrolling seems to cause content to not
render correctly when clicking a link or clicking on a search result
this separates the fix as according to commits it was for ios

only apply overflow-y to ios devices

this also seems to interfere with ICS
in ICS doing this stops the header from being fixed at the top of
the browser hence using fixed positioning and higher z-index to ensure
always over the content
